23/02/2011
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Several hundred people gathered on Tuesday (February 22nd) in Zagreb for an anti-government rally organised via the social network Facebook. The protestors demanded the government's resignation, the nationalisation of banks owned by foreigners, and salary hikes, among other things. Police prevented the demonstrators from reaching the government building. The rally organiser and four other people were detained for breaching public order. (Hina, Nova TV, Poslovni Dnevnik, tportal.hr - 22/02/11)
